cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with text matching and sentence representations. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it introduces a latent-variable model and employs deconvolutional networks for sequence decoding. Additionally, the use of deconvolutional networks suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as they are commonly used in image processing. Finally, the mention of optimization challenges and faster training suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
